lines.value: administrators also called sysops are active and regular who have access to technical features that help with maintenance
lines.name: Inuktitut

lines.value: administrators are expected to respect and be familiar with wikipedia policy as they are known and trusted members of the community
lines.name: Inuktitut

lines.value: they can protect and delete pages block other editors and undo these actions as well
lines.name: Inuktitut

lines.value: by default these privileges are granted indefinitely and are only removed under exceptional circumstances involving high level intervention see administrator abuse below
lines.name: Inuktitut

lines.value: ' ' in the very early days of wikipedia all users functioned as administrators and in principle they still should
lines.name: Inuktitut

lines.value: any user can behave in a way befitting an administrator provided they do not falsely claim to be one even if they have not been given the extra administrative functions
lines.name: Inuktitut

lines.value: from early on it has been pointed out that administrators should never develop into a special subgroup of the community but should be a part of the community like anyone else
lines.name: Inuktitut

lines.value: however they are equipped with a few more tools to do some chores that would potentially be harmful if everyone were entrusted with them
lines.name: Inuktitut

lines.value: over time standards to getting appointed administrator have risen but there are still several administrators created every week
lines.name: Inuktitut

lines.value: the community does look to administrators to perform essential housekeeping chores that require the extra access administrators are entrusted with
lines.name: Inuktitut

lines.value: among them are watching the and carrying out the consensus of the community on keeping or deleting these articles keeping an eye on new and changed articles to swiftly delete obvious vandalism and meeting user requests for help that require administrative access
lines.name: Inuktitut

lines.value: since administrators are expected to be experienced members of the community users seeking help will often turn to an administrator for advice and information
lines.name: Inuktitut

lines.value: in general administrators acting in this role are neutral
lines.name: Inuktitut

lines.value: they do not have any direct involvement in the issues they are helping people with
lines.name: Inuktitut

lines.value: when looking at a user's contributions a link that looks like [<u style="color:#002bb8">rollback ] - appears next to edits that are at the top of the edit history
lines.name: Inuktitut

lines.value: clicking on the link reverts to the last edit not authored by that user with an of reverted edits by x to last version by y and marks it as a minor change
lines.name: Inuktitut

lines.value: one click rollback is only intended for vandalism spam etc if reverting over disputed content it should be done manually with an appropriate edit summary

lines.value: * administrators can exclude bulk vandalism from ᐱᒋᕗᖅ ᐊᓯᐊᙳᑐᖅ recent changes
lines.name: Inuktitut

lines.value: to do this add &bot=1 to the end of the url used to access a user's contributions
lines.name: Inuktitut

lines.value: for example,
lines.name: Inuktitut

lines.value: when the rollback links on the contributions list are clicked the revert and the original edit that you are reverting will both be hidden from the default recent changes display
lines.name: Inuktitut

lines.value: the bot marker was originally added to keep massive edits from flooding recent changes hence the bot this means that they will be hidden from recent changes unless you click the bots link to set hidebots=0
lines.name: Inuktitut

lines.value: the edits are not hidden from contributions lists page histories or watchlists
lines.name: Inuktitut

lines.value: the edits remain in the database and are not removed but they no longer flood recent changes
lines.name: Inuktitut

lines.value: the aim of this feature is to reduce the annoyance factor of a flood vandal with relatively little effort
lines.name: Inuktitut

lines.value: this should not be used for reverting a change you just don't like but is meant only for simple vandalism particularly massive flood vandalism
lines.name: Inuktitut

lines.value: there are various other actions which only those with administrator privileges can perform
lines.name: Inuktitut

lines.value: if you have been around for a while and you would like sysop access add your name to according to the guidelines mentioned there and a discussion will take place by fellow editors in order to determine if there is consensus that you should become an administrator
lines.name: Inuktitut

lines.value: it is recommended that you write for wikipedia for a while before requesting administrator status since other users will have to recognize you before they can agree on trusting you with the tools
lines.name: Inuktitut

lines.value: also keep in mind that each has its own policies for administrators which may differ somewhat
lines.name: Inuktitut

lines.value: although are allowed on wikipedia in certain circumstances only one should have admin powers beyond being an editor
lines.name: Inuktitut

lines.value: be careful please
lines.name: Inuktitut

lines.value: if you are granted access you must exercise care in using these functions especially the ability to delete pages and their history to delete images and the ability to block ip addresses

lines.value: you should also take a look at the pages linked from the before using any of your admin abilities
